>> error_title = "@jrc03c/math/floor/tests"
>> error_is_fatal = "no"
>> success_title = "@jrc03c/math/floor/tests"

*html
	<h1 style="color: black; font-weight: bold;">
		All of these tests should pass:
	</h1>
	
>> pairs = []
>> pairs.add([0, 0])
>> pairs.add([1, 1])
>> pairs.add([1.0, 1.0])
>> pairs.add([234, 234])
>> pairs.add([-1, -1])
>> pairs.add([-1.0, -1.0])
>> pairs.add([-234, -234])
>> pairs.add([3.1, 3])
>> pairs.add([3.9, 3])
>> pairs.add([-3.1, -4])
>> pairs.add([-3.9, -4])

*for: pair in pairs
	>> x = pair[1]
	*program: @jrc03c/math/floor
	
	*if: x_floored = pair[2]
		>> success_message = "floor({pair[1]}) = {pair[2]}"
		*program: @jrc03c/show-success
	
	*if: not (x_floored = pair[2])
		>> error_message = "floor({pair[1]}) != {pair[2]}; instead returned {x_floored}"
		*program: @jrc03c/show-error

*button: Okay